    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3, attributable to the standardized single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 — this gap is accepted as inherent to the protocol and mitigated by the use of two independent laboratories. Uncertainty quantification completed for material and geometric input variability via Monte Carlo simulation; combined input uncertainty within acceptable bounds. Validation metric E/uval below 1.96 for all three QoIs. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory decision for this Medium model risk, Medium assurance level COU.",
